Thanedar recently introduced legislation to [abolish ICE](https://thanedar.house.gov/media/press-releases/congressman-shri-thanedar-introduces-the-abolish-ice-act), calling for the agency to be dismantled entirely. He told reporters that he believes "ICE is beyond reform." A [press release from his office](https://thanedar.house.gov/media/press-releases/congressman-shri-thanedar-to-introduce-abolish-ice-act) explains the act as a step toward creating a "more humane approach to immigration policy."

His comments come as ICE faces intense scrutiny from activists and Democratic leaders following [the death of Minneapolis woman](https://www.foxnews.com/politics/democrats-look-defunding-ice-impeaching-sec-noem-after-minneapolis-shooting) Renee Nicole Good during a confrontation with immigration agents earlier this month.

